---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SUPPORT_EMAIL, COMPANY_NAME } from '../config';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — AtLeast"
  description="Terms of service for AtLeast, the passive haptic timer for Apple Watch."
>
  <section class="px-6 py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
      <h1 class="mb-2 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight md:text-5xl">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="mb-12 text-sm text-brand-muted">Last updated: February 2026</p>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-base leading-relaxed text-brand-muted">
        <p>
          These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of the <em>AtLeast</em> application ("App") developed by {COMPANY_NAME} ("we", "us", "our"). By downloading or using the App, you agree to these Terms.
        </p>

        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-brand-text">Use of the App</h2>
          <p>
            <em>AtLeast</em> is a passive haptic timer designed for Apple Watch. The App is provided for personal, non-commercial use. You may not reverse-engineer, decompile, or disassemble the App, or use it for any unlawful purpose.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-brand-text">Health disclaimer</h2>
          <p>
            <em>AtLeast</em> is not a medical device. The App is intended as a general-purpose timer and should not be relied upon for health, safety, or medical decisions. Always use your own judgment during activities such as cold exposure, exercise, or meditation. If you have a medical condition, consult a healthcare professional before use.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-brand-text">Intellectual property</h2>
          <p>
            All content, design, and code in <em>AtLeast</em> are owned by {COMPANY_NAME} and protected by applicable intellectual property laws. You may not copy, modify, or distribute any part of the App beyond what is permitted by these Terms.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-brand-text">Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
          <p>
            The App is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, whether express or implied. We do not guarantee that the App will be uninterrupted, error-free, or compatible with all devices. Haptic feedback depends on hardware capabilities and system settings.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-brand-text">Limitation of liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, {COMPANY_NAME} shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from your use of the App. Our total liability shall not exceed the amount you paid for the App.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-brand-text">App Store terms</h2>
          <p>
            Your use of the App is also subject to Apple's standard End User License Agreement (EULA) and the App Store Terms of Service. In the event of any conflict, Apple's terms apply to the extent required.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-brand-text">Changes to these Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these Terms from time to time. Continued use of the App after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms. We encourage you to review this page periodically.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-brand-text">Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about these Terms? Email us at
            <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`} class="text-brand-accent underline">
              {SUPPORT_EMAIL}
            </a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
